ğŸ§  What is a Custom Hook?

A **Custom Hook** is a **JavaScript function** that:

* Starts with `use`
* Uses other hooks inside it
* Allows reuse of logic
* Makes components cleaner

ğŸ“Œ Custom Hook = Reusable Logic

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Why Do We Need Custom Hooks?

Without custom hooks:

* Code duplication
* Repeated useEffect logic
* Repeated state logic
* Hard to maintain

Custom hooks:
âœ” Keep components clean
âœ” Reuse logic
âœ” Improve readability

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Basic Custom Hook Example

useCounter Hook

```jsx
import { useState } from "react";

function useCounter(initialValue = 0) {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(initialValue);

  const increment = () => setCount(prev => prev + 1);
  const decrement = () => setCount(prev => prev - 1);

  return { count, increment, decrement };
}
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Using Custom Hook

```jsx
function Counter() {
  const { count, increment, decrement } = useCounter(0);

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>{count}</h2>
      <button onClick={increment}>+</button>
      <button onClick={decrement}>-</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Logic separated
ğŸ“Œ Clean component

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Custom Hook with useEffect

useFetch Hook (API Example)

```jsx
import { useState, useEffect } from "react";

function useFetch(url) {
  const [data, setData] = useState(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch(url)
      .then(res => res.json())
      .then(data => setData(data));
  }, [url]);

  return data;
}
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Using useFetch

```jsx
function Users() {
  const data = useFetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users");

  return (
    <div>
      {data && data.map(user => (
        <p key={user.id}>{user.name}</p>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Custom Hook Naming Rule

âœ” Must start with `use`
âœ” Example:

* useCounter
* useFetch
* useAuth
* useTheme

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Custom Hook for Form Handling

```jsx
function useForm(initialValues) {
  const [values, setValues] = useState(initialValues);

  const handleChange = (e) => {
    setValues({
      ...values,
      [e.target.name]: e.target.value
    });
  };

  return { values, handleChange };
}
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Custom Hook for Window Size

```jsx
function useWindowWidth() {
  const [width, setWidth] = useState(window.innerWidth);

  useEffect(() => {
    const handleResize = () => setWidth(window.innerWidth);
    window.addEventListener("resize", handleResize);

    return () => window.removeEventListener("resize", handleResize);
  }, []);

  return width;
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Good example of reusable logic

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Rules of Custom Hooks

âœ” Follow Rules of Hooks
âœ” Use only inside React components
âœ” Donâ€™t call inside loops/conditions
âœ” Start with `use`

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ†š Custom Hooks vs Normal Functions

| Normal Function | Custom Hook       |
| --------------- | ----------------- |
| No state        | Can use hooks     |
| Just utility    | Can manage state  |
| No lifecycle    | Can use useEffect |

